# Science SPARK Club Website - Customization Guide

Welcome to your new website! This guide will help you customize it with your own content.

## üìÅ What You Have

- **spark-website.html** - Your complete website in a single file
- All styling, animations, and functionality included
- Mobile-responsive design
- 25 activity slots (4 fully detailed examples, 21 templates to fill)

## üé® Quick Start

1. **Download** the spark-website.html file
2. **Open it** in any web browser to see it in action
3. **Edit it** using any text editor (Notepad, TextEdit, VS Code, etc.)
4. **Replace** placeholder content with your own

## üì∏ Adding Your Photos

### Where to Replace Photos:

1. **Mission Section** (Line ~950)
   - Find: `<div class="placeholder-img">Replace with photo of volunteers with students</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="your-photo.jpg" alt="Description" style="width:100%; border-radius:12px;">`

3. **Team Section - President** (Line ~1045)
   - Find: `<div class="placeholder-img" style="height: 350px;">Replace with president photo</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="president-photo.jpg" alt="President Name" style="width:100%; height:350px; object-fit:cover;">`

4. **Team Section - Officers** (Lines ~1060, 1075)
   - Find: `<div class="placeholder-img" style="height: 200px;">Replace with VP/officer photo</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="vp-photo.jpg" alt="VP Name" style="width:100%; height:200px; object-fit:cover;">`

5. **Team Section - Active Volunteers** (Lines ~1095-1180)
   - Find: `<div class="placeholder-img" style="height: 220px;">Replace with volunteer photo</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="volunteer1.jpg" alt="Volunteer Name" style="width:100%; height:220px; object-fit:cover;">`

6. **Team Section - All Volunteers (Compact)** (Lines ~1195-1270)
   - Find: `<div class="placeholder-img" style="height: 150px;">Photo</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="volunteer-name.jpg" alt="Name" style="width:100%; height:150px; object-fit:cover;">`
   - Add as many of these as you have volunteers!

7. **Team Section - Group Photo** (Line ~1280)
   - Find: `<div class="placeholder-img" style="height: 400px; width: 100%;">Replace with full team group photo</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="team-group-photo.jpg" alt="SPARK Team" style="width:100%; height:400px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:12px;">`

8. **Past Events** (Lines ~1320-1380)
   - Find: `<div class="event-image">Replace with event photo</div>`
   - Replace with: `<img src="event-photo.jpg" alt="Event" style="width:100%; height:250px; object-fit:cover;">`

### How to Add Photos:
- Put your photos in the same folder as the HTML file
- Reference them by filename: `<img src="lincoln-event.jpg" ...>`
- Or use online URLs: `<img src="https://yoursite.com/photo.jpg" ...>`

## ‚úèÔ∏è Editing Content

### Update Contact Email (Multiple places):
- Find: `spark@hillsdale.edu`
- Replace with your actual email

### Update Stats (Line ~890):
- Change numbers: `500+`, `15+`, `25+`, etc.
- Update descriptions

### Add Team Information (Lines ~1020-1300):

The team section now has **4 tiers** to handle large teams professionally:

**TIER 1 - Leadership Team (3 people):**
- **President** (large featured card):
  - Replace `[President Name]` with actual name
  - Add 3-4 sentence bio about their passion, goals, experience
  - Add inspirational quote
  - This card is special - it's bigger and highlighted with yellow border
  
- **Vice President & Officer** (smaller cards):
  - Replace names and titles
  - Add 2-3 sentence bios for each

**TIER 2 - Active Volunteers (6 people provided):**
- Medium-sized cards with photos
- Each needs: name, grade, specialty, 2-sentence bio
- These are your most active/regular volunteers
- You can add more by copying a volunteer card block

**TIER 3 - All Volunteers (Compact tiles - 8 provided, add as many as needed):**
- Small tiles with just: photo, name, and grade
- Perfect for showing ALL 20+ volunteers without cluttering
- **To add more volunteers:** Simply copy and paste one of the volunteer tile blocks
- Example tile block to copy:
```html
<div class="volunteer-tile">
    <div class="volunteer-tile-image">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="height: 150px;">Photo</div>
    </div>
    <h5>[Name]</h5>
    <p class="volunteer-grade">Junior</p>
</div>
```

**TIER 4 - Group Photo:**
- One large photo of your entire team together
- Add a caption about your team

**Tips for Large Teams:**
- Leadership (Tier 1): 2-3 people max
- Active Volunteers (Tier 2): 4-8 people
- All Volunteers (Tier 3): Everyone else (unlimited!)
- Group Photo (Tier 4): Whole team together

### Add/Edit Past Events (Lines ~1150-1200):
- Copy an event card block
- Paste to create a new event
- Update: date, school name, stats, description, testimonial

## üß™ Filling in Activity Templates

You have **4 fully detailed example activities** and **21 template slots** to fill.

### Template Locations:
Activities 5-25 (starting around line ~2500 in the JavaScript section)

### How to Fill an Activity:

1. **Find the template** (e.g., Activity 5: Volcano Eruptions)

2. **Replace bracketed text** with your content:
   ```javascript
   fullDescription: '[ADD FULL DESCRIPTION]'
   // Change to:
   fullDescription: 'Students create chemical reactions by mixing acids and bases...'
   ```

3. **Fill all sections:**
   - `fullDescription`: What students will do and learn
   - `whyItsCool`: What makes this exciting
   - `learningObjectives`: Array of 3-5 learning goals
   - `materials`: Array of all items needed
   - `steps`: Array of step-by-step instructions
   - `safetyTips`: Array of safety considerations
   - `engagementTips`: Array of teaching tips
   - `questionsToAsk`: Array of discussion questions

### Example of Filled Template:

```javascript
{
    id: 'activity-5',
    title: 'Volcano Eruptions',
    category: 'chemistry',
    difficulty: 'Easy',
    ageRange: 'K-6',
    duration: '30 minutes',
    icon: 'üåã',
    shortDescription: 'Create fizzing, foaming volcanic eruptions!',
    fullDescription: 'Students create a chemical reaction by combining baking soda (base) and vinegar (acid), producing carbon dioxide gas that creates an erupting volcano effect.',
    whyItsCool: 'It looks like a real volcano! Plus students can add food coloring for lava and dish soap for extra foam.',
    learningObjectives: [
        'Understand acid-base reactions',
        'Observe gas production from chemical reactions',
        'Learn about real volcanic eruptions'
    ],
    materials: [
        'Baking soda',
        'White vinegar',
        'Food coloring (red/orange)',
        'Dish soap',
        'Plastic bottle or cup',
        'Tray to contain mess',
        'Modeling clay (optional, to build volcano)'
    ],
    steps: [
        'Place plastic bottle on tray. Optional: build clay volcano around it',
        'Add 2-3 tablespoons baking soda to bottle',
        'Add a few drops of dish soap',
        'Add red/orange food coloring',
        'When ready to erupt: pour in 1/2 cup vinegar quickly',
        'Watch it fizz and foam out like lava!',
        'Discuss: What gas is being produced? (CO2)'
    ],
    safetyTips: [
        'Do this outside or on a protected surface',
        'Vinegar is safe but avoid getting in eyes',
        'Adult should pour vinegar for younger students',
        'No eating/drinking the materials'
    ],
    engagementTips: [
        'Build suspense before the eruption',
        'Let students make predictions',
        'Try different amounts - what makes the biggest eruption?',
        'Connect to real volcanoes around the world'
    ],
    questionsToAsk: [
        'What do you think will happen when we mix these?',
        'Why does it fizz?',
        'How is this like a real volcano?',
        'What gas is being created?'
    ]
}
```

## üé® Customizing Colors

Find the `:root` section (lines 20-35) and change colors:

```css
:root {
    --color-yellow: #FDB913;  /* Change to any color code */
    --color-teal: #06b6d4;
    --color-coral: #ff6b6b;
    --color-purple: #a78bfa;
}
```

Visit [coolors.co](https://coolors.co) to find color palettes!

## üåê Getting Your Site Online

### Option 1: Netlify Drop (Easiest - FREE)
1. Go to [app.netlify.com/drop](https://app.netlify.com/drop)
2. Drag your spark-website.html file onto the page
3. Get instant URL: `spark-science.netlify.app`
4. No account needed!

### Option 2: GitHub Pages (FREE)
1. Create free account at [github.com](https://github.com)
2. Create new repository named "spark-club"
3. Upload your HTML file (rename it to `index.html`)
4. Go to Settings > Pages > Enable GitHub Pages
5. Your site: `yourusername.github.io/spark-club`

### Option 3: Custom Domain
1. Buy domain (~$12/year): `sciencesparkclub.org`
2. Use Netlify or GitHub Pages
3. Point domain to your site

## üì± Testing Your Site

**Before going live, test:**
- Open on phone (is it readable?)
- Click all navigation links
- Open activity modals
- Try search and filters
- Replace ALL placeholder text with your content

## üÜò Common Issues

**Problem:** Photo won't show
- **Solution:** Make sure photo is in same folder as HTML, or use full URL

**Problem:** Activity doesn't open
- **Solution:** Check that the activity `id` is unique and matches

**Problem:** Colors look wrong
- **Solution:** Use # before color codes: `#FDB913` not `FDB913`

## üìù Checklist Before Launch

- [ ] Replace ALL placeholder images
- [ ] Add president information and photo
- [ ] Add volunteer team members (at least 4-6)
- [ ] Update email address everywhere
- [ ] Fill in at least 10 activities (you can add more later)
- [ ] Update stats with real numbers
- [ ] Add at least 3 past events
- [ ] Test on mobile phone
- [ ] Check spelling and grammar
- [ ] Add your social media links (if any)

## üí° Tips

- **Start small:** You don't need all 25 activities filled immediately
- **Add as you go:** Update after each school visit
- **Save often:** Make backup copies as you edit
- **Ask for help:** If stuck, share the file with someone tech-savvy
- **Team organization:** The 4-tier team structure lets you showcase everyone:
  - Tier 1 (Leadership): Your president and officers get spotlight
  - Tier 2 (Active): Regular volunteers with bios
  - Tier 3 (Everyone): Simple tiles for all 20+ volunteers
  - Tier 4 (Group): Team photo brings it all together
- **Adding volunteers is easy:** Just copy/paste a volunteer tile in Tier 3!

